The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 22, 2004 				 Grasim plans garment exports 
 A STAFF REPORTER				 	 Krishnamoorthy in Calcutta on Monday. A Telegraph picture																								Calcutta, June 21: Grasim Industries Ltd plans to diversify into 100 per cent export-oriented readymade garments in the current financial year.																								Chief operating officer S. Krishnamoorthy said, the flagship of the AV Birla group is looking at the potential of exporting readymade garments, especially to Europe and the US.																								We intend to enter the readymade segment and whatever is produced in the first few years will be exported, he said.																								The readymade garments export plan is in response to the planned phaseout of textile quotas from January 1.																								Krishnamoorthy has also said the companys plan to enter the readymade garments segment will not cannibalise the brands from Madura Coats, another AV Birla outfit.																								The company is also looking at China  a country with a vast potential for textiles.																								We have decided to have a person in Shanghai. We are looking at exporting synthetic material and importing high-quality fabric from China, he said. 
